<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Raymond_Smullyan&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7" title="Edit section: Bibliography">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Bibliography</span></h2>
<ul>
<li><i><a href="http://www.mit.edu/people/dpolicar/writing/prose/text/godTaoist.html" class="external text" title="http://www.mit.edu/people/dpolicar/writing/prose/text/godTaoist.html" rel="nofollow">Is God a Taoist?</a></i> by Raymond Smullyan, 1977.</li>
<li><i><a href="http://www-cs-faculty.stanford.edu/~knuth/smullyan.html" class="external text" title="http://www-cs-faculty.stanford.edu/~knuth/smullyan.html" rel="nofollow">Planet Without Laughter</a></i> by Raymond Smullyan, 1980.</li>
<li><i><a href="http://www.mit.edu/people/dpolicar/writing/prose/text/epistemologicalNightmare.html" class="external text" title="http://www.mit.edu/people/dpolicar/writing/prose/text/epistemologicalNightmare.html" rel="nofollow">An Epistemological Nightmare</a></i> by Raymond Smullyan, 1982.</li>
</ul>
